<TITLE> Shares fall across the board </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)Markets ended lower on the first trading day of the month pulled down mainly by a slump in bank shares that account for almost half the market capitalisation. The country's twin bourses saw almost 70 percent of the traded scrips lose on Sunday. Brokerage house officials said prices across the board fell with some issues rising discretely on speculations of dividends. Issues of Beximco rose on declaration of dividend. Beximco announced 10 percent cash dividend along with stock dividends at 50 percent. Beximco Pharmaceuticals and Shinepukur Ceramics both declared 10 percent cash and 20 percent stock dividend while Beximco Synthetics offered 15 percent stock dividend. The group's Z category issue, Bextex Ltdm announced 10 percent stock dividend for the year. The day also saw Bangladesh Thai Aluminum, Bangladesh Hotels and Aramit declare year-ending declarations. Turnover on the twin bourses rose significantly from the previous trading session. Dhaka Stock Exchange saw shares worth Tk 4.87 billion changing hands, up from Thursday's Tk 3.72 billion. DSE's benchmark general index shot up 15 points at the very outset of the trading followed by a downward trend across the day. It lost 15.18 points or 0.59 percent to close at 2539.16. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2110.04, falling 9.81 points or 0.46 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 shed 18.04 points or 0.91 percent to finish on 1958.79. Losers outnumbered gainers 165 to 67 while eight issues held steady. Summit Power remained topped issues in terms of turnover with shares worth Tk 652.045 million traded. It rose 5.68 percent to Tk 1380.50. Beximco followed with a turnover of Tk 530.774 million to gain 6.76 percent on Tk 277.80. State-owned Titas Gas ended on Tk 526.50, slipping 0.51 percent. It saw shares worth Tk 410.420 million traded. Shinepukur Ceramics saw shares traded to the tune of Tk 247.573 million to ended on Tk 105.80, up 6.43 percent. Eastern Housing Ltd saw turnover worth Tk 237.645 million. It surged 7.99 percent to close at Tk 628.25. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardBeximco Pharmaceuticals, S Alam Cold Rolled Steels, Summit Alliance Port Ltd and Bextex Ltdfinished higher on buying pressure. Social Investment Bank fell as investors locked in profits. Chittagong Stock Exchange Turnover on Chittagong Stock Exchange rose to Tk 655.730 million from Tk 453.826 million on last week's closing day. The CSCX or selective categories index fell 21.24 points or 0.39 percent to close at 5326.67. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8205.10, down by 22.74 points or 0.27 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip plunged 68.68 points or 1.06 percent to finish at 6357.76. Of the traded issues, 101 declined, 38 advanced with three scrips unchanged. Beximco Ltd topped the turnover board, with shares worth Tk 9.16 million traded. Shinepukur Ceramics, Bextex Ltd, Beximco Synthetics and AB Bank were the other turnover leaders.
